               <msContents>
                  <summary>F<locus target="#3r">fols. 3r, </locus>-157r: Psalter. F<locus target="#3r">3r, </locus>-135v: 151 Psalms of David. The word for God is unrubricated. The midpoint of the Psalter is marked by a later hand which circled the line in pencil. Psalm 151 is the short version. F<locus target="#136r">136r, </locus>-149v: 15 Biblical Canticles. Canticle four is "Prayer of Hana, mother of Samuel, prophetess." F<locus target="#149v">149v, </locus>-157r: Song of Songs, common version. F<locus target="#158r">158r, </locus>-170v: Praises of Mary, arranged for the days of the week: Monday (158r), Tuesday (159r), Wednesday (161r), Thursday (163v), Friday (166r), Saturday (167v), Sunday (169r).  F<locus target="#170v">170v, </locus>-176r: Gate of Light. Varia: <locus target="#1r">1r, </locus>: Excerpt from Praises of Mary. <locus target="#135v">135v, </locus>: A copy of the inscription on a bell given by Emperor Failadas (1632-1667) to the Church of St. Cyriacus of Wance Bahr, in Ge'ez, but by a later hand. <locus target="#157v">157v, </locus>: A deleted note in Ge'ez. <locus target="#176v">176v, </locus>: note deleted so thoroughly that the language cannot be determined. <locus target="#177v">177v, </locus>: Note in Amharic concerning the recitation of the Psalter. Ornamental designs, f<locus target="#3r">3r, </locus>, 62v, 75r, 84r, 90r, 104v, 118v, 121v, 128v, 136r, 149v, 157r, 176r. Crude cross, <locus target="#177r">177r, </locus>. <locus target="#3b">3b</locus>: note of ownership by Walda Giyorgis (including information from Macomber, Catalogue).</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1"><locus from="3r" to="157r" facs="003">Fols 3r–157r</locus><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2701Dawit">Psalter</title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ'ǝz</textLang>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1"><locus from="3r" to="135v" facs="003">Fols 3r–135v</locus><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur">Mazmura Dāwit</title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ'ǝz</textLang>
                </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2"><locus from="136r" to="149v" facs="136">Fols 136r–149v</locus><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1828Mahale">Book of Odes</title>
