                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <locus target="#1r" facs="001">Fol. 1r</locus>
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    Excerpt from <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2509Weddas">Wǝddāse
                                                  Māryām</title>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <locus target="#Inside cover" facs="001">Fols. Inside, </locus>
                    <desc>
                    The inside cover of the book has a mirror niche carved into the wood
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <locus target="#3r #62v #75r #84r #90r #104v #118v #121v #128v #136r #149v #157r #176r" facs="003 063 075 084 090 105 119 122129 136 150 157 176">Fols. 3r, 62v, 75r, 84r, 90r, 104v, 118v, 121v, 128v, 136r, 149v, 157r, 176r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    Ornamental designs
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <locus target="#177r" facs="177">Fol. 177r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    crude cross
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a4">
                    <locus target="#3v" facs="004">Fol. 3v</locus>
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    note of ownership by <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ ጊዮርጊስ</foreign>, Walda Giyorgis, the original owner
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <locus target="#69r" facs="069">Fol. 69r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    The midpoint of the Psalter is marked by a later hand that circled the line in pencil
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a5">
                    <desc>
                    Psalm 151 has only the first of the four plusses that constitute the long version
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a6">
                    <locus target="#135v" facs="136">Fol. 135v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    A copy of the inscription on a bell given by Emperor Failadas (1632-1667) to the Church of St. Cyriacus of Wance Bahr, in Ge'ez, but by a later hand. Text: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዝመረዋት ዘንጉሠ ነገሥት ፋሲለደስ ዘወሀቦ ለቅዱስ ቂርቆስ ዘወንጤ ባሕር ከመ ይኩኖ ለመድኀኒተ ሥጋ ወነፍስ</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a7">
                    <desc>
                    Canticle four is “Prayer of Hana, mother of Samuel, prophetess.”
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <locus target="#157v" facs="158">Fol. 157v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    A deleted note in Ge'ez
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <locus target="#176v" facs="177">Fol. 176v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    note deleted so thoroughly that the language cannot be determined
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a9">
                    <locus target="#177v" facs="178">Fol. 177v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    Note in Amharic concerning the recitation of the Psalter
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a10">
                    <desc>
                    This entry employs some information from Macomber, William F. “Catalogue of oriental manuscripts in the library of Seabury-Western Theological Seminary, Evanston, Illinois.” Le Muséon 92 (1979) 369–386
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
